Make the description a bit clearer, and directly/indirectly give them the written out numbers, everyone knows how to write the numbers 0 to 9 => is time saving:


You need to decrypt a string of numbers called [[hidden]].

For every {{2}} numbers do:
<<1:>> convert the first number into its [[name]] ("zero", "one", “two", "three", "four", "five", "six", "seven", "eight", "nine");
<<2:>> get from the [[name]], the character with index the second number (<<zero-indexed>>). 

<<IMPORTANT>>: number {{99}} represents a space-character.

For example:
- in case of 32, we convert the 3 into {{"three"}} and 2 into {{r}};
- in case of 90, we convert the 9 into {{"nine"}} and 0 into {{n}};
- in case of 03, we convert the 0 into {{"zero"}} and 3 into {{o}}.
